  "prompt": "I did really bad on my 1st term of 11th (cbse).If I pull myself together and do really well on the other 2 terms can I still get above 95% at the end?",
  "response": "Yes, it is possible to achieve an overall percentage above 95% if you perform exceptionally well in your remaining terms. The CBSE grading system typically allows for the best two terms to significantly impact your overall percentage. Here are some steps to help you maximize your performance:\n\n1. **Assess Your Current Situation**: Review your performance in the first term, identify areas of weakness, and understand which subjects require more focus.\n\n2. **Create a Study Plan**: Develop a structured study plan that allocates time for each subject, focusing more on the areas where you need improvement.\n\n3. **Consistent Study Habits**: Maintain a regular study schedule. Consistency is key to retaining information and mastering difficult concepts.\n\n4. **Practice Regularly**: Solve sample papers, previous years\u2019 question papers, and mock tests to get familiar with the exam pattern and improve time management.\n\n5. **Seek Help When Needed**: Don\u2019t hesitate to ask teachers or peers for help if you\u2019re struggling with specific topics.\n\n6. **Stay Motivated and Positive**: Keep a positive mindset and stay motivated. Set achievable goals for each study session.\n\n7. **Focus on Revision**: As the exams approach, ensure you allocate time for revision to reinforce what you\u2019ve learned.\n\n8. **Take Care of Yourself**: Ensure you maintain a healthy balance with proper sleep, nutrition, and relaxation to keep your mind fresh.\n\nIf you commit to your studies and execute your plan effectively, there\u2019s a strong chance you can improve your performance and achieve your goal. Good luck!",
